  "body": "Running `npm ci` on Github actions fails because ethereumjs-abi pulls from github repositories rather than npm. Here's a snippet from the package-lock.json:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n            \"eth-sig-util\": {\r\n              \"version\": \"1.4.2\",\r\n              \"resolved\": \"https://registry.npmjs.org/eth-sig-util/-/eth-sig-util-1.4.2.tgz\",\r\n              \"integrity\": \"sha1-jZWCAsftuq6Dlwf7pvCf8ydgYhA=\",\r\n              \"dev\": true,\r\n              \"requires\": {\r\n                \"ethereumjs-abi\": \"git+https://github.com/ethereumjs/ethereumjs-abi.git\",\r\n                \"ethereumjs-util\": \"^5.1.1\"\r\n              }\r\n            },\r\n            \"ethereumjs-abi\": {\r\n              \"version\": \"git+https://github.com/ethereumjs/ethereumjs-abi.git#ee3994657fa7a427238e6ba92a84d0b529bbcde0\",\r\n              \"from\": \"git+https://github.com/ethereumjs/ethereumjs-abi.git\",\r\n              \"dev\": true,\r\n              \"requires\": {\r\n                \"bn.js\": \"^4.11.8\",\r\n                \"ethereumjs-util\": \"^6.0.0\"\r\n              },\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis can be circumvented by forcing Github to use https instead of ssh in the Github Action, as such:\r\n\r\n```yml\r\n    steps:\r\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v2\r\n\r\n      - uses: actions/setup-node@v2\r\n        with:\r\n          node-version: 14.x\r\n\r\n      - name: Reconfigure git to use HTTP authentication\r\n        run: >\r\n          git config --global url.\"https://github.com/\".insteadOf\r\n          ssh://git@github.com/\r\n\r\n      - name: Lint, test and compile\r\n        run: |\r\n          npm ci\r\n```\r\n\r\nNot sure if this is something you guys can fix, or if it's a downstream dependency, but wanted to share in case anyone runs into similar issues.",
